# Superstore Return Rate Analysis
### Tableau | Data Storytelling | Business Intelligence

---

## 📌 Project Overview

This project analyzes product return rates for a fictional retail company (Superstore) to identify the root causes of high returns and provide actionable business recommendations. Built as part of the TripleTen Data Analytics program (Sprint 5).

The final deliverable is a multi-page Tableau Story that walks stakeholders through the data like an executive presentation — from problem identification to strategic recommendations.

---

## 🎯 Business Problem

> *What is causing high return rates, and what can leadership do about it?*

Returns are costly. This analysis surfaces which products, customers, categories, and regions are driving returns — so decision-makers can act with confidence.

---

## 📊 Charts & Visualizations Built

| # | Chart Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Scatterplot | Sales vs. Return Rate by Sub-Category |
| 2 | Bar Chart | Return Rate by Product Category |
| 3 | Bar Chart | Return Rate by Top 10 Customers |
| 4 | Map | Geographic Distribution of Returns by State |
| 5 | Dual-Axis | Return Rate Over Time (Monthly Trend) |
| 6 | Heatmap | Return Rate by Category × Month |
| 7 | Dual-Axis | Total Returns vs. Return Rate by Month |

**Plus:** Interactive Dashboard, Full Tableau Story, and Mockup Sheets (1–7)

